Problem Statement
You are in the position of a Senior Data Platform Engineer and have the role of ensuring code quality as well as sharing knowledge with more junior team members. Imagine that a beginner has been assigned the task of writing code for an ETL workflow. The objective is:
Extract transaction data (credit card, debit, payments in general) daily from a relational database.
Filter transactions where status = 'success'and perform a count grouped by the typecolumn.
Load the data into a file system in a columnar format. 
The source table has variable volume and may reach tens of millions of rows per day. 

Your task is to review and detect problems in the following piece of code
